    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_vm.01575.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <date when="1891-01-01">New Year's Day 1891</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>My Dear Mr Whitman</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I can not let the New Year go by without wishing you "A <hi rend="underline">Happy
                    Happy</hi> New Year" and a <hi rend="underline">lot</hi> of them I feel sure,
                that if you could enjoy <hi rend="underline">all</hi> the New Years that your
                friends would like to see you enjoy&#8212;that you would have eternal life&#8212;<pb
                    xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_vm.01576.jpg" type="verso"/>I expect to make a visit
                to Camden in a few months, and look forward with a good deal of pleasure to calling
                on you&#8212;</p>

            <closer>
                <salute>affectionately yours</salute>
                <signed>John W. Wroth</signed>
                <name type="place">4 W 90 St</name>
                <name type="place">New York</name>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="loc_vm.01577.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="loc_vm.01578.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text>
